snippet.textDisplay:
I know most of the MTV Coke Studio songs are dual themed (fusion) i.e. a modern theme and a traditional theme. In most of the cases, either one of them is excellent while the other one is OK (e.g. Badri Badariyan, Zariya etc) or else both are excellent (e.g. Saathi Salaam, Kattey, Rabba, Mauje Naina etc).

But I must say, this song was totally messed up by that lady...!
While the start is so amazing (rather stunning with that guitar composition), as soon as she takes over I feel like changing the song... I mean why did she push so much on the irritating classical side? It's really annoying to hear her classical screaming, she hurts my ears and spoils my mood so bad, I am literally planning to trim the song (my local mp3 file) and crop the part starting from when she takes over (3:03) until she stops screaming (5:29) ..!!!

Damn it MTV, you should know better than that...may be Coke Studio folks are not really from Music background, but we expected better from you...!!!
